1. Introduction
1.1 Project Overview
The Tukii Transport System is a modern, responsive static website designed to showcase an urban transport service specializing in eco-friendly tuktuk rides. The website provides comprehensive information about the service, including booking procedures, pricing, safety measures, and customer support options.

1.2 Purpose
This user manual serves as a comprehensive guide to understanding and navigating the Tukii Transport website. It documents all features, pages, and functionality available to users, providing clear instructions for accessing information and understanding the transport service offerings.

1.3 Target Audience
End Users: Potential customers seeking transport services
Administrators: Team members managing content and updates
Developers: Technical personnel maintaining the codebase
Stakeholders: Business owners and decision-makers
2. System Overview
2.1 System Architecture
The Tukii Transport System is built using modern web technologies with a focus on simplicity, performance, and user experience. The architecture consists of:

Core Technologies:
HTML5: Semantic markup for content structure
CSS3: Advanced styling with gradients, transitions, and responsive design
Google Fonts (Lexend): Modern, readable typography
Unsplash Images: High-quality photography integration
2.2 Key Features
Fully responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop devices
Eight interconnected pages with consistent navigation
Professional UI/UX with modern design principles
Optimized for readability and accessibility
Fast loading times with no external dependencies except fonts and images
Clean, maintainable code structure
2.3 Design Philosophy
The design follows contemporary web standards with emphasis on:

Simplicity: Clean layouts without unnecessary complexity
Consistency: Uniform styling and navigation across all pages
Readability: Optimal typography and spacing
Visual Hierarchy: Clear information architecture
Modern Aesthetics: Professional appearance suitable for a transport business
