3.2 Browser Compatibility
The website is compatible with all modern browsers:

Google Chrome (version 90+)
Mozilla Firefox (version 88+)
Safari (version 14+)
Microsoft Edge (version 90+)
Opera (version 76+)
3.3 Responsive Breakpoints
Device Type	Screen Width	Behavior
Mobile	< 640px	Single column layout, stacked navigation
Tablet	641px - 968px	Adapted two-column layouts, wrapped navigation
Desktop	> 968px	Full multi-column layouts, horizontal navigation
4. Page-by-Page Guide
4.1 Home Page (index.html)
Purpose
The home page serves as the primary landing page for the Tukii Transport website. It provides visitors with an immediate understanding of the service through compelling visuals and clear messaging.

Key Sections
Navigation Bar: Persistent top navigation with logo and links to all pages
Hero Section: Full-width image with overlay, headline, tagline, and call-to-action button
Why Choose Tukii: Four feature cards highlighting service benefits
Built for the City: Image and text section showcasing vehicle features
Statistics: Key metrics (50K+ riders, 200+ vehicles, 15 cities, 4.9★ rating)
Footer: Company info, quick links, and contact details

User Interaction
Users land on this page when visiting tukii.com
Hero section immediately communicates the value proposition
Call-to-action button directs users to booking page
Feature cards provide quick overview of service benefits
Statistics build trust and credibility
Navigation allows users to explore other sections
Design Note: The hero section uses a high-quality image of a tuktuk on a city street with a dark gradient overlay to ensure text readability while maintaining visual impact.
4.2 About Page (about.html)
Purpose
The About page tells the Tukii story, communicating the company's mission, values, and commitment to sustainable urban transport. It helps build trust and connection with potential customers.

Key Sections
Page Hero: Title and subtitle introducing the section
Company Story: Background on Tukii's founding and growth
Image Banner: Full-width city street photography
Mission & Vision Cards: Two-column layout explaining purpose and goals
What Sets Us Apart: Six value propositions in grid layout
Impact Section: Environmental and social impact metrics
Leadership Team: Introduction to company leadership

Content Highlights
Mission Statement:
"To revolutionize urban mobility by providing accessible, sustainable, and delightful transportation experiences that benefit riders, drivers, and communities alike."

Core Values:
Electric-First: 100% clean electric power fleet
Driver Partnership: Fair compensation and benefits
Technology Integration: Smart routing and tracking
Community Focus: Local hiring and partnerships
Safety Standards: Rigorous vetting and training
Transparent Pricing: No surge pricing or hidden fees
4.3 Services Page (services.html)
Purpose
The Services page provides comprehensive information about all transport solutions offered by Tukii, helping users understand which service best fits their needs.

Key Sections
Point-to-Point Rides: Large card with image and features
Hourly Rentals: Flexible rental options with details
Service Grid: Six additional services in card format:
Airport Transfers
City Tours
Group Transport
Package Delivery
Corporate Accounts
Accessible Transport
Service Availability: Operating hours for different services

Service Details
Service	Best For	Key Features
Point-to-Point	Daily commutes, quick trips	5-min pickup, GPS tracking, climate control
Hourly Rental	Multiple errands, appointments	Dedicated driver, flexible routing
Airport Transfer	Flight pickups/drop-offs	Flight tracking, 60-min wait time, 24/7
City Tours	Sightseeing, exploration	Knowledgeable drivers, custom routes
4.4 Pricing Page (pricing.html)
Purpose
The Pricing page provides transparent, detailed pricing information for all services, building trust through clarity and eliminating concerns about hidden costs.

Key Sections
Introduction: Statement on transparent pricing philosophy
Standard Rides Table: Base fare and per-kilometer rates
Hourly Rentals Table: Pricing for 2, 4, and 8-hour packages
Special Services Cards: Three featured pricing cards for airport transfer, city tour, and package delivery
Discounts Section: Four discount types (Student, Senior, Frequent Rider, Group)
Good to Know: Important pricing notes and policies

Pricing Structure
Standard Ride Calculation:
Base Fare: $4.50 (covers first 2 km)

Per Kilometer: $1.80 (after initial 2 km)

Wait Time: $0.40/min (after 3 free minutes)

Example: A 10 km ride = $4.50 + (8 × $1.80) = $18.90

Important: All prices include taxes, fees, and gratuity. No surge pricing is applied during peak hours or special events.
4.5 Safety Page (safety.html)
Purpose
The Safety page demonstrates Tukii's commitment to passenger and driver safety through comprehensive protocols and transparent communication of safety measures.

Key Sections
Driver Excellence Program: Large feature with image showing vetting and training processes
Safety Grid: Four cards covering:
Vehicle Standards
Smart Technology
Health Protocols
Insurance Coverage
Emergency Support: Three emergency response options in dark-themed section
Safety Tips for Riders: Before, during, and after ride guidance
Reporting & Response: Incident reporting procedures


Key Safety Features
Category	Measures
Driver Screening	Background checks, 5+ years experience, monthly training, drug testing
Vehicle Maintenance	Weekly inspections, monthly checks, vehicles under 3 years old
Technology	GPS tracking, in-app SOS button, incident detection, trip sharing
Insurance	$2M liability, passenger accident coverage, property protection
Emergency Contact: 24/7 emergency support available at +1-800-TUKII-911 for immediate assistance.
4.6 Booking Page (booking.html)
Purpose
The Booking page guides users through various methods of booking a ride, providing clear instructions and setting expectations for the booking process.

Key Sections
Booking Methods: Three primary ways to book:
Mobile App (featured with app badges)
Web Booking
Phone Booking
How It Works: Four-step process visualization
Booking Tips: Two-column tips for availability and special requirements
Payment Options: Four payment methods grid
Cancellation Policy: Clear policy explanation
Corporate & Group Bookings: Enterprise services information

Booking Process Steps
Enter Details: Provide pickup location, destination, time, and special requirements
Get Quote: Receive instant fare estimate with no hidden fees
Confirm Ride: Review details and receive driver information
Track & Ride: Watch driver approach in real-time and enjoy the ride
Payment Methods Accepted:
Credit and debit cards (encrypted and secure)
Cash (exact change appreciated)
Mobile wallets (Apple Pay, Google Pay)
Corporate billing (monthly invoicing)
4.7 FAQ Page (faq.html)
Purpose
The FAQ page addresses common questions and concerns, reducing support burden and helping users find answers quickly.

Key Sections
Questions are organized into five categories:

Booking & Rides: 5 questions about booking process and ride details
Pricing & Payment: 5 questions about fares and payment methods
Safety & Comfort: 5 questions about safety measures and comfort features
Technical & Account: 5 questions about app usage and account management
Special Services: 4 questions about accessibility and specialized offerings

Sample FAQ Entries
Q: How do I book a ride?
A: You can book through our mobile app, website at tukii.com/book, or by calling +1-800-TUKII-GO. The app offers the fastest booking experience with instant confirmation and real-time tracking.

Q: Do you have surge pricing?
A: No. We believe in transparent, consistent pricing. Our rates remain the same during peak hours, bad weather, and special events.

Q: Are pets allowed?
A: Small pets in carriers are welcome at no extra charge. Medium to large pets require advance notice. Service animals are always welcome and never require prior approval.

